description: Was responsible for system performance, simulation design, and software engineering test and evaluation efforts related to accuracy model development and analysis activities associated with the TRIDENT Submarine Launched Ballistic Missile weapon and navigation systems. Development of this model was very closely related to the missile flight test program. The model was used to conduct pre-flight accuracy predictive analysis for both pad and submarine-launched flight tests. Also, he performed post-flight analyses by processing data (based on cumulative flight test program accuracy as well as stellar sighting observables) from these tests and reviewing "quick look" test reports.
